## When to use
Use this skill when you need to check active network connections on your system.

## Approach
Utilize the shell_exec tool to run the 'netstat -anp | grep ESTABLISHED' command. This will provide information about all established network connections along with their process IDs.

## Example
```shell
shell_exec('netstat -anp | grep ESTABLISHED')
```

## Pitfalls
Ensure that the netstat command is available on your system and may need root privileges to see detailed connection information.